The paper focuses on assessing trust in online social networks, which involves analyzing complex social network topologies and conducting accurate assessments. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges of handling trust in online networks, which could also place it in the Security and Cryptography (cs.CR) category. The paper also proposes a model for trust assessment, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper uses real-world datasets to validate the proposed model, which could place it in the Databases (cs.DB) category. Overall, the most likely categories are cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.CR, cs.DB, and cs.AI.
